Hatashita Open
November 18th, 2007

          Judo Saskatchewan is proud to announce two silver and three bronze medals from our 13 fighters Saturday November 17 and one bronze medal from four fighters competing Sunday November 18th in Seniors. The Hatashita Open in Toronto, Ontario is an international tourament with 800 competitors registered.

          Juvenile Female -41 athlete Alex Poliakiwski won four matches and lost one match resulting in a Silver medal.

          Juvenile Female -57 Emily Schaan won one match and lost 2 resulting in a fifth place finish.

          Female -62 Nicole Dyke won two and lost two finishing in fifth place.

          IJF Women -48 athlete Jordan Poliakiwski today won two matches 2 and lost one resulting in a silver medal.

          Juvenile Men -45 Warren Seib won two matches and lost 2 resulting in a bronze medal.

          Andrew Yuen -60 won 5 matches and lost one resulting in a bronze medal, Dilyaver Sheykhislyamov won 4 lost 1 resulting in a bronze medal.

          Alex Delorme won one match and lost two and finished in fifth place.

          Judo Saskatchewan Athletes: Bishop Sommerfeld, Ashley McBride, Kendal McArthur, Matthew Ferneaux, and Emin Sheykhislyamov also competed Saturday November 17 2007.

          On Sunday November 18 2007 Dilyaver Sheykhislyamov won 5 lost 1 resulting in a second bronze medal.

          Nichelle Stever won two and lost two finishing in fifth place, Ian MacDonald won 3 lost 2, Emin Sheykhislyamov won two and lost two.
